                "id": "R26OMZOTMD04UD",
                "title": "Best DAC for the price",
                "body": "I've had some decent DACs in my time, also I have a friend with some high end expensive ladder DACs and a well thought out audio room and system so I have experience listening to combinations of high end audio. This SU-1 DAC performs really well compared to everything within reason. When I listen to my speakers set up in the \"magic triangle\" and some well recorded stereo tracks I can hear instruments and vocals coming from the right position in the image and its slightly forward and holographic. The sound is natural and detailed without being bright. I think to get a better DAC than this you will have to spend hundreds more for very small gains. The only gripe I have is the USB-C input is both for power and data. If you have an electronically noisy power supply some people have reported audio noise floor in some rare cases. For my computer with a Seasonic Platinum PSU I hear no noise from the speakers/DAC/amp combo I'm using. The power should be separate from the USB data so it could be powered by a separate low noise PSU but I get that this is DAC is all about budget so its acceptable. Read more",
